Fifth National Conference and Exposition on
ELECTRONIC DATA INTERCHANGE FOR GOVERNMENT

ELECTRONIC COMMERCE:
HELPING TO REINVENT GOVERNMENT

September 12-15, 1994
Hyatt Regency Bethesda -- Washington, D.C.

Featuring:
- Sessions of technology applications and management issues
- Practical "how to" ideas for government agencies and vendors
- In depth management seminars and technical workshops
- Status Update: Federal Electronic Commerce Acquisition Team
- Top speakers from government and industry
- Free exhibits by leading suppliers

Don't miss the one event covering developments in government's
growing usage of electronic commerce!

Sponsored by: Data Interchange Standards Association (DISA)

Managed by: U.S. Professional Development Institute

Official Publication: EDI World

Welcome!  The Conference sponsor is pleased to invite you to attend the
only major conference dedicated to the use of electronic commerce/EDI by
federal agencies. This national event will focus on issues, applications
and implementation of emerging technologies in the federal government.

WHAT YOU WILL LEARN
- Current status of electronic data interchange
- How leading agencies are implementing EDI
- How to interface EDI with existing systems
- Required hardware and software
- What type of application package to consider
- EDI standardization and security issues
- How to sell EDI to agency management
- Government-wide trends and issues

WHO SHOULD ATTEND
- Information Resource Managers and Planners
- Security and Paperwork Management Specialists
- Accounting and Financial Managers
- Contracting and Disbursing Officers
- Management and Systems Analysts
- Suppliers and Contractors to Federal Agencies
- Controllers and Cost Accountants
- Communications Managers and Analysts

CONFERENCE FORMAT
This leading conference on EDI and the federal environment is organized to
benefit managers,technical/communications specialists, accounting and
contracting professionals. Separate briefings and workshops focus on
special interest areas, while the larger conference gives attendees a
chance to expand their knowledge of technical information, management
techniques and practical applications.
The entire event will be organized as follows:
Pre-Conference Management Briefings
September 12, 1994
EDI Conference & Exposition
September 13 & 14, 1994
Post-Conference Technical Workshops
September 15, 1994

